'''Kevin Christley''' is a member of the [[501st Legion (fan organization)|501st Legion]], where he is the former Editor in Chief of the 501st Legion's ''Static Burst'' magazine and former Detachment Leader of the 501st Special Operations Detachment. He's also a member of the [[Rebel Legion]] and the current Restoration Lead for [[Lucasfilm Ltd.|Lucasfilm's]] 3/4-scale [[T-65 X-wing starfighter/Legends|T-65 X-wing starfighter]] based out of the Wings over the Rockies Air Museum at Lowry, Colorado. The X-wing fighter has been displayed at ''[[Star Wars]]'' [[Celebration (1999)|Celebration]], [[Celebration III]], and [[Celebration IV]]. Kevin is featured on page 174 of the 2008 Guinness Book of World Records as the 501st Legion [[stormtrooper]] proudly carrying the flag of Finland in Lucasfilm's entry at the 2007 Rose Parade.

He authored the article "[[Inside the 501st]]," published in [[Star Wars Insider 96|''Star Wars Insider'' 96]], and often works with Lucasfilm and their marketing partners, such as M&M Mars and [[Del Rey]], to coordinate volunteer staffing at promotional events.

